[3] Diarrhea, fatalities, indigenous population - Colombia (Risaralda)
Date: Mon 31 Dec 2012
Source: Noticiero Caracol [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JG, edited]
http://www.caracol.com.co/noticias/regional/mas-de-15-ninos-indigenas-de-risaralda-han-muerto-por-diarrea-y-fiebres/20121230/nota/1817551.aspx


More than 15 indigenous children in Risaralda died because of diarrhea and febrile disease. The Health Secretary mentioned that they have not acknowledged this situation affecting the Embera Chami ethnic group, which, together with malnutrition has also taken the lives of 8 adults.

Delfin Arce, a member of the Embera ethnic group and main officer of the Regional Indigenous Council of Risaralda, said -- after traveling along the Purembara area within Mistrato District -- that many people in the affected area are quite ill because of this fever and diarrheal disease.

Children are the most affected group, followed by adults among which 8 deaths have been reported. No support has been received yet from Risaralda healthcare facilities, whose jurisdiction includes the Mistrato District.

Mr Arce declared he was quite disconcerted by this occurrence, which, together with malnutrition, greatly affects the health of Embera Chami people living in this area of the country.

On the other hand, Lina Beatriz Rendon-Torres, Risaralda health secretary, who declared she had no information about the situation reported by Mr Arce, immediately ordered the implementation of a healthcare team to be sent to Purembara and its surrounding areas, in order to control this outbreak.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The etiology of this outbreak among an indigenous people in west central Colombia is not clear. With fever, disease due to salmonellosis or shigellosis should be considered but the differential diagnosis is substantial.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/4H4f. - Mod.LL]
